-- Options Volatility Rises as Oil Prices Swing Most in Two Weeks
-- B y   B a r b a r a   P o w e l l
-- 2013-03-18T18:44:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/options-volatility-rises-as-oil-prices-swing-most-in-two-weeks.html
Crude options volatility rose,
after touching below 17 percent on March 15, as underlying
futures prices swung the most in two weeks today.  Implied volatility for at-the-money options expiring in
May, a measure of expected price swings in futures and a gauge
of options prices, was 17.75 percent at 12:49 p.m. on the  New
York  Mercantile Exchange. It ended at 17.33 percent March 15.  West Texas Intermediate crude for May delivery rose 13
cents to $93.95 a barrel at 1:48 p.m. on the Nymex, after
ranging from $92.14 to $94.30 as the market absorbed reports
that finance ministers in the euro area reached an agreement on
March 16 forcing depositors to share in the cost of the latest
bailout of Cyprus. The $2.16 range was the widest since Feb. 25.  The move to $94.30 was the highest price since Feb. 25. The
range of the previous two weeks was $89.78 to $94.20.  “Right now, the market has been trading in a range and the
volume will go down,” said  Phil Flynn , senior market analyst at
Price Futures Group in  Chicago . “The market doesn’t have a
direction.”  The most-active options in electronic trading today were
May $98 calls, which fell 2 cents to 5 cents a barrel on volume
of 1,309 contracts at 2:25 p.m. May $90 puts were the second-
most active with 1,222 lots. They dropped 11 cents to 61 cents a
barrel.  Puts, Calls  Calls made up 53 percent of electronic-trading volume. In
the previous session on March 15, calls accounted for 51 percent
of the volume.  May $94 calls were the most active options traded in the
previous session, with 5,841 contracts changing hands. They rose
21 cents to $1.86 a barrel. May $85 puts were unchanged at 19
cents a barrel on 5,347 lots.  Open interest was highest for December $105 calls with
36,134 contracts. Next were June $90 puts at 32,058 and June
$120 calls at 30,032.  The exchange distributes real-time data for electronic
trading and releases information the next business day on open-
outcry volume, where the bulk of options activity occurs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
